args:
The siblings find the road to Chanzelia blocked
by fiends consumed by black mana. The beasts'
coordination suggests someone pulling their
strings, but a sudden call from Leonidas urges
the siblings back to the Halidom for now.
Yes, just through the canyon ahead and\nwe'll be at Chanzelia's doorstep.
Ugh, finally we can take a civilized rest...
You almost make it sound as if you've done\na lick of work. It only gets harder from\nhere, dear brother.
There's the matter of the frenzied fiends,\nmanaging the refugees... Not to mention\nformulating a plan to face the Progenitor.
I should think our plates rather too full to\nbe slacking.
The Alberian royal siblings return to South\nGrastaea with a landship full of refugees driven\nfrom Grams by the Progenitor's rebirth.
Yet those displaced people are but one of the\nthorny problems they carry with them on the road\nto Chanzelia.
That's all well and good to say, but surely\nspending every moment fretting isn't the\nanswer, either? I say rest while we still—
A pack of fiends has appeared, sir! They've\nblocked the ship's path and are preparing\nto flank us!
It seems the time for resting is already\npast.
I'll go and carve us a path. To be both\nshield and beacon to the defenseless is\nmy duty as one born of royal blood.
That would be all of us, Valyx. We'll go\ntogether.
I should think you'd be champing at the bit\nto lead the people of Grams back to\nDyrenell, Your Emperorship? Now move.
Wha—Y-yes, but wait a moment! I'm not\nemotionally prepared to... DON'T LEAVE\nME BEHIND!
...The situation is grave, my liege. We\nmust act swiftly!
The fiends afflicted with black mana grow\never more violent, and Alberia's largest\ncities are all attacked at once...
Tempting as it is to frame it all as simply\nthe reverberations of the Progenitor's\nreturn, I fear there's more at play here.
Though driven to frenzy by the black mana,\nthe fiends thus far have been just that:\nwild beasts, acting on animal instinct.
But this latest attack is clearly different.\nTiming, location, the smart distribution of\nforces... It's all too strategic to be instinct.
(Is the Progenitor controlling them? No...\nAccording to Chelle's intelligence, he still\nhasn't moved from Grams.)
(What's more, the reports don't paint him\nas the sort to bother forming a strategy just\nto be rid of us.)
(But if that's the case, who is guiding the\nfrenzied fiends?)
...Conjecture won't lead to any answers.\nYou. Gather my siblings at once.
I don't relish the idea of turning to them\nfor aid with this, but we haven't the time\nfor pride. Be off with you!
...Hmph. This is going to be a headache.
That takes care of this area. Now all that\nremains is...
Eep?! Why should I have to endanger\nmyself in this lunacy?!
Ohhh! A dragon, felled in a single blow!
Heh heh ha ha ha, watch how they flee\nbefore us! With brother Phares at my side,\nwe've nothing to fear!
*sigh*... Indeed. Were they truly nothing\nbut fiends and dragons, that may well have\nbeen the case.
Huh? Er... Noticed what? J-just so I can be\nsure you're talking about the same thing I\nnoticed.
I suspect that was a scouting force, meant\nto gauge our strength. ...Someone is\ncontrolling them from the shadows.
Seeing as they timed their attack just as\nwe entered the canyon, our opponent\nclearly knows the terrain here well.
Blocked fore and aft by fiends and by rock\nwall on either side, we would have no\nchoice but to fight... Infuriating, but smart.
...A-ah, yes! So it WAS the same thing I\nwas just about to bring up!
Urgent enough to require shouting it?\n...Well, what is it?
Yes, ma'am! His Highness Leonidas asks\nthat all members of the Alberian royal\nfamily gather at the Halidom at once!
He'll have noticed what's going on as well,\nthen.
If it's that urgent, I don't suppose we have\ntime to stop at Chanzelia first.
Noooo, I was so ready to finally get a\nproper rest in Chanzelia...
Enough bellyaching. Back aboard the Gran\nFiore now, march! We leave at once.
